Neural ICE OTA trust anchors (ICE-Fabric ADR-0026 / PLAN-ADR-0026-SIGNING — P0)
===============================================================================

This directory holds the PUBLIC keys the appliance uses to verify signed OTA
update bundles before applying them. The keys are staged here at the Owner key
ceremony (P0) — they are NOT generated by, or shipped from, this repository:

  ota-root.pub   OTA root key (offline, hardware-token-held). Verifies the
                 signed bundle manifest and the signed channel record. This is
                 the authoritative gate: no bundle is authorized without it.

  image-ci.pub   CI image key. Verifies per-image cosign signatures on images
                 we build — defense in depth UNDER the root-key gate, never a
                 substitute for it.

Only public keys ever live here. Private keys never touch the device or this
repository.

Behavior of the on-device verifier (`ni-ota-verify`, P2) when a key file is
missing or empty:

  - enforce=0 (shadow mode — the default in /etc/neural-ice/ota.conf): the
    verifier LOGS the verification failure and lets the update proceed.
  - enforce=1: the verifier REFUSES the update (fail-closed).
